com.ikueb.mapextractor

Class MapExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ikueb.mapextractor.MapExtractor

  • public final class MapExtractor
extends java.lang.Object
    An utility class providing:
    • A set of helper methods to easily convert Streams of CharSequences to either Properties or Map instances.
      • These methods operate on streams and reproduces the parsing logic in Properties.load(java.io.Reader) as closely as possible. The only differences are no support for multi-element values and the default key delimiter can only be escaped with "\" once.
    • A set of collectors to be used in Stream.collect(Collector) as terminal operations.
      • These methods are meant to be drop-in replacements for the standard JDK Collectors.toMap() methods, but with a regex prefixed argument to split each stream element into key-value pairings.
    • A MapExtractor.Parser parser implementation for facilitating quick, 'one-shot' CharSequence-to-Map conversions.
      • Whereas the methods and collectors above adhere more closely to line-based processing, where each stream element is a line, this uses the notion of 'records', where a stream element may contain more than one record.

      • with

        public static MapExtractor.Parser<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> with(java.lang.String rs,
                                                                          java.lang.String fs,
                                                                          java.lang.String ofs)
        The returning implementation applies toKey() and toValue() mappers on the resulting fields as well. Combining values of duplicate keys is done as such:
        1. If the output field separator (ofs) is passed as null , the more recent value of duplicate keys will be used.
        2. If either value is empty, the other value will be used.
        3. Otherwise, String.join(CharSequence, CharSequence...) is used. This is done so that there will not be any superfluous separators in the final value.
        Parameters:
        rs - the record separator to use
        fs - the field separator to use
        ofs - the output field separator to use
        Returns:
        a MapExtractor.Parser implementation defined with the method arguments
        See Also:
        toKey(), toValue()
